{
  "texts": [
    "This type of research utilizes general-purpose foundation LLMs (e.g., Llama) and a substantial volume of table-related data for instruction tuning.",
    "Table tuning examples include TableLlama [11] and Table-GPT [12].",
    "• Code tuning addresses table processing tasks from a code generation perspective by generating code (e.g., SQL or Python) to manipulate table data.",
    "Code tuning examples include Magicoder [64], Lemur [44], and DAAgent [17].",
    "• Hybrid of table and code research reveals that table instruction tuning based on code LLMs is more effective, i.e., code LLMs are tuned using table instruction datasets."
  ]
}